 {"id":"br-r37-c1-j6qpf","title":"parity: draw_bipartite signature divergence — fnx requires top_nodes positionally, nx accepts only **kwargs","description":"fnx.draw_bipartite has signature (G, top_nodes, pos=None, **kwds) where top_nodes is a required positional arg, but networkx.drawing.nx_pylab.draw_bipartite has (G, **kwargs). Drop-in calls like nx.draw_bipartite(G) work in nx but fnx raises TypeError missing positional argument top_nodes. Fix: align signature to (G, **kwargs) and pull top_nodes out of kwargs (or compute it via bipartite_sets if absent), so fnx accepts the same call shape as nx.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T04:28:46.975023293Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T04:49:45.891385685Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T04:49:45.889512479Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 097c007: draw_bipartite now (G, **kwargs) matching nx; top_nodes pulled from kwargs and inferred via bipartite_sets if absent. 170 smoke tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-k147g","title":"parity: NodeView/DegreeView reprs stringify node IDs; AtlasView/AdjacencyView reprs uninformative","description":"Several view-class __repr__ implementations diverge from nx: (1) NodeView repr converts node IDs to strings — repr(G.nodes) on path_graph(3) returns NodeView(('0', '1', '2')) instead of nx's NodeView((0, 1, 2)). The actual stored values ARE integers; only the repr lies. (2) DegreeView has the same stringification bug — DegreeView([('0', 1), ('1', 2), ...]) vs nx's DegreeView({0: 1, 1: 2, ...}). (3) EdgeView repr shows count format 'EdgeView(2 edges)' vs nx's 'EdgeView([(0, 1), (1, 2)])'. (4) AtlasView/AdjacencyView reprs fall through to default '<franken_networkx.AtlasView object at 0x...>' instead of nx's AtlasView({1: {}}). Drop-in debugging output, repr-snapshot tests, and any tooling that compares __repr__ output break. Fix: override __repr__ at class level from Python on NodeView, DegreeView, EdgeView, AtlasView, AdjacencyView.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T08:25:45.558574576Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T08:34:28.707191667Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T08:34:28.705244871Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit 1431c3b. NodeView/DegreeView reprs now show original-typed node IDs; EdgeView reprs show actual edge tuples with per-graph-type prefixes (EdgeView/OutEdgeView/MultiEdgeView/OutMultiEdgeView); AtlasView/AdjacencyView reprs show the underlying mapping. 13 parity tests freeze the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-k3khk","title":"parity: triangles dict iterates in sorted-key order, nx iterates in node-insertion order","description":"fnx.triangles returns a dict with keys sorted (e.g. for edges added in (2,3),(0,1),(1,2),(3,4) order: [0, 1, 2, 3, 4]) regardless of node-insertion order. nx returns the dict in node-insertion order ([2, 3, 0, 1, 4]). Same iteration-order family fixed in br-r37-c1-pm78h (communicability_betweenness_centrality), br-r37-c1-f6epo (second_order_centrality), and br-r37-c1-9fa26 (core_number). Drop-in code that relies on iteration order matching nx breaks. Fix: reorder result dict in iteration order of G.nodes().","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T10:29:18.945207791Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T10:31:33.997745276Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T10:31:33.995763976Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit df1fca1. triangles now iterates in node-insertion order matching nx. 6 parity tests freeze the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
